elements.title: Cello Sonata
elements.contents: ... that Claude Debussy (pictured) described his Cello Sonata, composed within a few weeks in July 1915 at a Normandy seaside town, in a letter to his publisher Durand as of "almost classical form"?

elements.title: Royce Williams
elements.contents: ... that after U.S. Navy pilot Royce Williams engaged in a solo dogfight with seven Soviet MiG-15s during the Korean War, he was ordered never to tell anyone about it?

elements.title: Tomoi
elements.contents: ... that the 1985 manga series Tomoi contains the first depiction of HIV/AIDS in any literary medium in Japan?

elements.title: Eunice Newton Foote
elements.contents: ... that the unacknowledged contributions of Eunice Newton Foote to climate change research were recovered by Elizabeth Wagner Reed, whose research in genetics were also obscured?

elements.title: sensory friendly

elements.title: Gilbert Eastman
elements.contents: ... that American educator Gilbert Eastman, who acted in and wrote American Sign Language plays, won an Emmy Award in 1993?

elements.title: Huliya
elements.contents: ... that Nirmalendu Goon shared his doubts about Sheikh Mujibur Rahman's political decisions during the 1969 East Pakistan mass uprising in his poem Huliya?

elements.title: Chaz Stevens
elements.contents: ... that after Florida schools banned 54 mathematics books, Chaz Stevens petitioned that they also ban the Bible?
